10 Section 1. R.S. 18:1309(J)(1) is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
11 §1309. Early voting; verification
12 * * *
13 J.(1) Upon approval of the secretary of state, a registrar of voters may utilize
14 commissioners selected and trained by the registrar of voters to assist the registrar
15 during the early voting period in the conduct of early voting by his office, including
16 conducting the nursing home early voting program pursuant to R.S. 18:1333. A
17 registrar of voters shall, in seeking the approval of the secretary of state, indicate to
18 the secretary the number of commissioners that is required for such assistance. A
19 commissioner who assists the registrar in the conduct of early voting shall take an
20 oath of office as a deputy registrar for the early voting period and shall complete an
21 affidavit prepared by the secretary of state that contains the name, address, and last
